This article [[Article description::describes update the microcode of AMD processors.]]

== Installation ==

=== Firmware ===

Install {{Package|sys-kernel/linux-firmware}}:

{{Emerge|sys-kernel/linux-firmware}}

=== Kernel ===

You need to activate the following kernel options:

{{KernelBox|1=
Processor type and features  --->
    [*] /dev/cpu/microcode - microcode support
    [ ]   Intel microcode patch loading support
    [*]   AMD microcode patch loading support

Device Drivers  --->
    Generic Driver Options 
        (amd-ucode/microcode_amd.bin amd-ucode/microcode_amd_fam15h.bin amd-ucode/microcode_amd_fam16h.bin) External firmware blobs to build into the kernel binary
        (/lib/firmware) Firmware blobs root directory
}}

You can now reboot your computer with the new kernel.

